Author: Timo#5756
Content: Hey there!

Author: Markus#5464
Content: Hey!

Author: Timo#5756
Content: I would like to talk about the Komodo Oracle. Is there someone from the dev team open for a discussion?

Author: FishyGuts#5085
Content: @jl777c

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: ok

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: @Timo what questions do you have

Author: Timo#5756
Content: On the article about komodo oracles vs. other oracle projects, it says there is a flaw on how they are build. I find it hard comparing the komodo oracle to something like Chainlink. Do they both serve they same use cases? Based on the article from komodo, it seems like it's for price-feed only

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: I've used one to track a dog.

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: and have a few for tracking vote stats, notaristaion, coin migrations etc - http://oracle.earth/sh_vote_graph/

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: chainlink uses data aggregation, which is the level that our oracles CC is for

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: to get a trustless oracle, you need to do something like what we do and it would apply for anything that has an online data source

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: stuff i've done was befre KMD oracles were upgraded to trustless

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: as far as use cases go, there is room for both trusted, aggregated and trustless oracles

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: but working on upgrades

Author: Timo#5756
Content: Yeah I would get into the trustelss/decentralization part when comparing it to Chainlink. Aggregation is only one component for securing the network. The other two big parts are stake and reputation

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: and something wont be so easy to make a trustless oracle for due to lack of freely available online data source

Author: Timo#5756
Content: Why do you think Chainlink is not secure enough/not trustless (enough)?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: stake and reputation add detection and disincentives, but doesnt prevent an attacker

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: as i said chainlink and oracles CC are sufficient in many cases

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but if the betsize dwarves the value of the stake, then it is not a deterrent, is it?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if the attacker is patient and builds up reputation over months or years, it doesnt prevent that, does it?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: things are on a spectrum

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: there are no absolutes

Author: Timo#5756
Content: How does it not prevent an attacker? Reputation raises the weight of the people acting honest and want to earn money. On the long term, raising your reputaiton brings you more 'jobs' and thus more income through the node. An attacker would have to 'farm' reputation for a long while to even consider attacking and maybe losing his stake

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: what if he is betting 10x or 100x the value of the stake/reputation?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this model caps the entire at risk amount to the value of the stake, but there is no way to measure off chain bets

Author: Timo#5756
Content: "Betsize higher then stake", how would that happen? If I as a dApp developer could set the stake the nodes have to have, for providing my dApp with their data, I can have it always higher than the value behind it

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so the stake/reputation systems work quite well, until it doesnt

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: offchain betting

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: lets say I make a bet with you about next years world cup, we happen to be both billionaries, so we bet a billion dollars sidebet,

Author: Timo#5756
Content: It's about onchain for now. Offchain is not a thing yet. Chainlink didn't build into that direction yet. Main use case is onchain

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but you cant stop offchain

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: since it is offchain

Author: Timo#5756
Content: So when it's about onchain, you would say reputation and staking is more secure/ secure enough?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: and offchain bets can and will influence onchain, you certainly cant guarantee that nobody would ever make sidebets offchain
